title: Spotify's Top 10 most viral tracks
text:
The Canadian Press - ONLINE EDITION Spotify's Top 10 most viral tracks By: The Associated Press Report Error 
The following list represents the most viral tracks on Spotify, based on the number of people who shared it divided by the number who listened to it, from Friday, Oct. 9, to Thursday, Oct. 15, via Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and Spotify. 
CANADA 
1. B & Steve, "Home Run Anthem" (Wax Records) 
2. Lady Leshurr, "Queen's Speech 4" (Lady Leshurr) 
3. DNCE, "Cake by the Ocean" (Republic Records) 
4. Gnash featuring Olivia O'Brien, "I Hate U I Love U" (Gnash) 
5. Ruth B, "Lost Boy" (Columbia Records) 
6. TroyBoi featuring Diplo and Nina Sky, "Afterhours" (Mad Decent) 
7. The Weeknd featuring Eminem, "The Hills (Remix)" (Republic Records) 
8. Haley Reinhart, "Can't Help Falling in Love" (red dot) 
9. Kacy Hill, "Foreign Fields" (The Island Def Jam Music Group) 
10. She Wants Revenge, "Tear You Apart" (Flawless / Geffen Records) 
UNITED STATES 
1. DNCE, "Cake by the Ocean" (Republic Records) 
2. Louis the Child featuring K.Flay, "It's Strange" (Next Wave Records) 
3. Haley Reinhart, "Can't Help Falling in Love" (red dot) 
4. Bit Funk featuring Shae Jacobs, "Off the Ground" (Universal Music Canada Inc.) 
5. William Singe, "679" (Over Media) 
6. Kurt Cobain, "And I Love Her" (Universal Music Enterprises, LLC) 
7. Leslie Odom Jr., Anthony Ramos, Daveed Diggs, Okieriete Onaodowan, Lin-Manuel Miranda, Christopher Jackson, Phillipa Soo, Original Broadway Cast of Hamilton, "Alexander Hamilton" (Atlantic / WEA) 
8. Tate Kobang, "Bank Rolls (Remix)" (300 Entertainment) 
9. Tyler Ward featuring Two Worlds, "Watch Me (Whip / Nae Nae) (Acoustic)" (mudhutdigital.com) 
10. Charles Kelley with Dierks Bentley and Eric Paslay, "The Driver" (Capitol Records Nashville) 
UNITED KINGDOM 
1. Jamie Lawson, "Wasn't Expecting That" (Gingerbread Man Records) 
2. William Shatner, "Common People" (Shout! Factory LLC) 
3. KDA featuring Tinie Tempah and Katy B, "Turn the Music Louder (Rumble) (Radio Edit)" (Ministry of Sound Recordings Ltd.) 
4. WSTRN, "In2" (Atlantic Records UK) 
5. The 1975, "Love Me" (Interscope Records) 
6. Haley Reinhart, "Can't Help Falling in Love" (red dot) 
7. Stephen, "Fly Down" (Halfway House) 
8. She Wants Revenge, "Tear You Apart" (Flawless / Geffen Records) 
9. Joe Gilgun, Vicky McClure, Chanel Cresswell, Danielle Watson, "Wanky Shank" (UMC (Universal Music Catalogue)) 
10. Perry Fitzpatrick featuring Michael Socha, "Sniffbanging" (UMC (Universal Music Catalogue)) 
GLOBAL 
1. Carl Deman, "Vafan" (Linc Music) 
2. Kurt Cobain, "And I Love Her" (Universal Music Enterprises, LLC) 
3. DNCE, "Cake by the Ocean" (Republic Records) 
4. Haley Reinhart, "Can't Help Falling in Love" (red dot) 
5. Yall featuring Gabriela Richardson, "Hundred Miles" (Sony Music Entertainment) 
6. Louis the Child featuring K.Flay, "It's Strange" (Next Wave Records) 
7. Sofi Tukker, "Drinkee" (HeavyRoc Records) 
8. Leslie Odom Jr., Anthony Ramos, Daveed Diggs, Okieriete Onaodowan, Lin-Manuel Miranda, Christopher Jackson, Phillipa Soo, Original Broadway Cast of Hamilton, "Alexander Hamilton" (Atlantic / WEA) 
9. Gnash featuring Olivia O'Brien, "I Hate U I Love U" (Gnash) 
10. Tate Kobang, "Bank Rolls (Remix)" (300 Entertainment)
